Rule 1: The N stage for breast cancer is determined by the number of positive lymph nodes.
Rule 2: N0 indicates no regional lymph node metastasis.
Rule 3: N1 indicates regional lymph node metastasis with 1 to 3 positive axillary lymph nodes.
Rule 4: N2 indicates regional lymph node metastasis with 4 to 9 positive axillary lymph nodes.
Rule 5: N3 indicates regional lymph node metastasis with 10 or more positive axillary lymph nodes.
Rule 6: The size of the metastatic deposit in the lymph node does not affect the N stage in breast cancer.
Rule 7: Extracapsular extension does not affect the N stage in breast cancer.
